<subSubSection id="3796656070D4FF32FF23EF108878FDF0" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7F3336EB70D4FF32FF23EF108878FDF0" blockId="170.[151,1436,289,565]" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D4FF32FF23EF108B44FE9B" bold="true" box="[199,335,325,350]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
This relatively young fossil from the Quaternary period (present to 2.5mya) almost certainly belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D4FF32FE61EF3F881AFE44" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[389,529,362,385]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Liometopum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D4FF32FE61EF3F881AFE44" box="[389,529,362,385]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Liometopum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D4FF32FD7DEF3C8921FE44" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[665,810,361,385]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D4FF32FD7DEF3C8921FE44" box="[665,810,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The illustration of the front of the head (Nazarw et al., 1994, fig. 2a) is typical of modern 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D4FF32FDCEEFDB8919FE60" box="[554,786,397,421]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Liometopum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D4FF32FDCEEFDB88BDFE60" box="[554,694,398,421]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Liometopum</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, with small anteriorly placed eyes and a roughly cordate head capsule which is narrowed at the mandibles (although slightly more than modern species) (
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D4FF32FB0FEFE48ADFFE28" author="Del Toro, I. &amp; Pacheco, J. A. &amp; Mackay, W. P." pageId="170" pageNumber="171" pagination="299 - 369" refId="ref110435" refString="Del Toro, I., Pacheco, J. A., Mackay, W. P. (2009) Revision of the ant genus Liometopum (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Sociobiology, 53, 299 - 369." type="journal article" year="2009">Del Toro et al., 2009</bibRefCitation>
). While the figure shows only a top view of the body, this is also consistent with general 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D4FF32FB36EF838F55FE28" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1234,1374,470,493]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Liometopum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D4FF32FB36EF838F55FE28" box="[1234,1374,470,493]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Liometopum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphology. Until a more detailed study of the actual specimen can be undertaken, it seems appropriate to transfer this species from 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D4FF32FEC8EC488BB6FDF0" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[300,445,541,565]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D4FF32FEC8EC488BB6FDF0" box="[300,445,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D4FF32FE04EC4B8867FDF0" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[480,620,542,565]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Liometopum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D4FF32FE04EC4B8867FDF0" box="[480,620,542,565]" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Liometopum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
